dcterms:creator: Daniel Gildea
Daniel Jurafsky
dcterms:description: The CoNLL-2009 dataset is a benchmark for semantic role labeling, providing annotated data for both English and Chinese languages, including predicted POS tags and predicate disambiguation.
dcterms:title: CoNLL-2009

dcterms:creator: Daniel Gildea
Daniel Jurafsky
dcterms:description: The CoNLL-2009 English dataset is a subset of the CoNLL-2009 benchmark specifically for the English language, used for training and evaluating semantic role labeling models.
dcterms:title: CoNLL-2009 (English)

dcterms:creator: Daniel Gildea
Daniel Jurafsky
dcterms:description: The CoNLL-2009 Chinese dataset is a subset of the CoNLL-2009 benchmark specifically for the Chinese language, used for training and evaluating semantic role labeling models.
dcterms:title: CoNLL-2009 (Chinese)

dcterms:creator: Daniel Gildea
Daniel Jurafsky
dcterms:description: The CoNLL-2009 dataset with predicted POS tags includes annotations for part-of-speech tagging, which are essential for semantic role labeling tasks.
dcterms:title: CoNLL-2009 (predicted POS tags)

dcterms:creator: Daniel Gildea
Daniel Jurafsky
dcterms:description: The CoNLL-2009 dataset includes a predicate disambiguator for English, which helps in identifying the correct sense of predicates in semantic role labeling.
dcterms:title: CoNLL-2009 (predicate disambiguator for English)

dcterms:creator: Daniel Gildea
Daniel Jurafsky
dcterms:description: The CoNLL-2009 dataset includes a predicate disambiguator for Chinese, which assists in determining the correct sense of predicates in semantic role labeling.
dcterms:title: CoNLL-2009 (predicate disambiguator for Chinese)
